---
description: Dbt score normalization keeps backward compatibility
globs: dbt/models/**/*.sql
alwaysApply: false
---

# Dbt Score Normalization Contract

- When normalizing any score to a new 0-10 scale, compute and expose a `raw_*` version for debugging (e.g. `raw_demand_score`).
- In the mart layer, keep the original column name/value for backward compatibility unless the Streamlit dashboard is updated in the same change.
- If an output column name changes (e.g. `gap_score` -> normalized value), update the Streamlit query/columns together so the UI does not break.

